    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-24T14:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-24T14:45:00-05:00" n="130"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/71: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-24T14:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.19 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s September 20, 5 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d130fn23">Not
                        printed.</note> Nicaraguan Government apparently is complying with its
                    agreement and has no patrol in Las <pb facs="0217" n="115" xml:id="pg_115"/>
                    Trojas. I shall continue to make it clear to the President that his guards et
                    cetera are not to proceed farther than the zone occupied by them on May 20th,
                    1918.</p>
                <p>Honduran Chargé d’Affaires stated to me that he did not anticipate any further
                    difficulties. His relations with Chamorro<note n="24" xml:id="d130fn24">Gen.
                        Emiliano Chamorro, President of Nicaragua.</note> are very cordial.</p>
                <p>I do not believe that there will be any further trouble here regarding this
                    matter. All is apparently progressing in a very satisfactory manner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
